main event: An unidentified object was observed at Duluth AFB on 5th October 1967, appearing brighter and larger than a star, changing from red-orange to white.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 1.5 hours,The object was described as round and comparable in size to one-eighth of a full moon,The object was seen by multiple witnesses including air police,The object moved slowly up and down and faded at dawn,No physical evidence or photographs were collected.
witness description: 2/LT Eric Olson, SSGT Kickerbocker, and Mr. ***, along with five other air police
